cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods, specifically Random Forest, for gene selection in microarray data analysis. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the stability of selection, which is related to database systems (cs.DB) and computational efficiency (cs.CE). Finally, the use of Random Forest for gene selection is also relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
